Part 1: What Happens During Training?

Imagine you have a dataset of 10,000 images of cats and dogs.

The neural network cannot magically understand the data all at once. It follows a repetitive cycle:

Training Data
      ↓
Take some samples
      ↓
Forward Propagation
      ↓
Calculate Loss
      ↓
Backpropagation
      ↓
Update Weights
      ↓
Repeat until all data is seen
      ↓
Start over if needed

This repeated process introduces the concepts of batch size and epochs.

Part 2: What is an Epoch?
Definition

An epoch is one complete pass through the entire training dataset.

Suppose you have:

Total training samples = 1000

If the model processes all 1000 samples once, then:

1 Epoch = The model has seen every training example exactly once.

Example

Dataset:

Image1, Image2, Image3, ..., Image1000

After the model has trained on all 1000 images:

Epoch 1 completed ✅

It may then start over:

Epoch 2 → sees all 1000 images again.
Epoch 3 → sees all 1000 images again.
Why Multiple Epochs?

Think about studying for an exam.

Suppose you read a textbook only once.

You understand some concepts.
You forget others.

If you revise the same book multiple times:

Your understanding improves.
You make fewer mistakes.

A neural network behaves similarly.

Epoch	Model Understanding
1	Knows almost nothing
5	Learns basic patterns
20	Learns deeper relationships
100	May even start memorizing the data

This last point leads to an important concept:

Too Few Epochs → Underfitting

The model hasn't learned enough.

Too Many Epochs → Overfitting

The model memorizes the training data instead of learning general patterns.

Part 3: What is Batch Size?
Definition

A batch is a small group of training examples processed together before updating the weights.

Instead of feeding all 1000 examples at once, we split them into smaller chunks.

Suppose:

Dataset size = 1000 samples.
Batch size = 100.

Then the model processes:

Batch 1 → Samples 1-100
Update weights

Batch 2 → Samples 101-200
Update weights

...

Batch 10 → Samples 901-1000
Update weights

After all 10 batches are processed:

1 Epoch is complete.
